  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, a crime exacerbated by their position as an accountant who inherently holds fiduciary responsibilities. However, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration during sentencing. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating that this behavior is out of character. Furthermore, the defendant has shown remorse and has already made partial restitution to the victim. Recognizing the need for a sentence that balances deterrence and punishment with rehabilitation, a brief period of incarceration is warranted to acknowledge the severity of the fiduciary breach, followed by probation to allow the defendant to continue working and fully repay the stolen funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
